postcontent:
The North Carolina Concealed Carry Class is open to law abiding U.S. Citizens who are at least 21 years of age and wish to carry a concealed handgun for their personal or family’s safety. In this course, you will gain the required knowledge of handgun safety, along with learning about responsible carry and how to gain the needed proficiency skills with a firearm. Also there will be instruction on the laws and the obligations of the concealed handgun carrier. Upon the successful completion of this course you will receive a certificate from the NC Justice Academy which will be needed to apply for a Concealed Carry Handgun Permit with the Sheriff’s office in the county you reside.

You need to bring: A handgun along with at least 50 rounds of reliable ammunition along with hearing and eye protection. A valid and correct NC Drivers License or NC State ID card must be presented during class. Students completing this course will receive a certificate from the NC Justice Academy.

The NC CCH course is 8+ hours with a class fee of $70 and $60 for Active/Prior Military, Fire, Police and Hospital Workers. 

Rental Guns are available for use with ammunition for a nominal fee.

We also teach private lesson as well as the NRA Pistol, Rifle, Shotgun, Home Defense, Firearm Safety, Range Safety Officer and Personal Protection inside the home.

title: For Sale:  Seekins Precision Factory Upper Tunable w 15" MCSR
postcontent:
Awesome competition/suppressor ready brand new Seekins Precision AR15 upper with 15" MCSR V2 Keymod rail and adjustable gas block. This is a high quality factory built upper actually assembled by Seekins Precision. If you don't know who that is, do your research - they manufacture very high end components (they make a lot of the parts for other companies such as Spikes Tactical and many others). The extremely lightweight 15" MCSR V2 Keymod rail is well over $200 alone (has a 1.8" inside diameter to accommodate suppressors), and the Seekins adjustable gas block is another $60 and offers you tremendous tuning capabilities (see below). Upper is complete with melonite treated full milspec M16 bolt carrier group and charging handle. This upper should shoot a 1 inch group if you can. Throw this on any lower with a decent trigger and have an amazing competition level rifle built by one of the top quality manufacturers in the industry. $650 cash takes it. 

The Seekins Precision Adjustable Gas Block lets you to fine tune your rifle's gas system for smoother cycling and operation. Regulating the amount of gas used to cycle the action allows tuning the rifle’s operation to a specific load and the use of low mass bolt carriers, buffers and springs to reduce felt recoil. This is critical to allow faster follow up shots, target acquisition and reliability.
The Seekins Precision Adjustable Gas Block is field adjustable. Operation is easy, simply turn the gas regulating screw in to lessen the amount of gas and out to add more gas, then use the brass set screw to lock the setting in place. The overall height of the gas block is 1.37” with left to right dimensions at .94” to fit under most hand guards and still have the customization of an adjustable gas block.
Melonite Coated to reduce wear and corrosion for extended periods of fire, it also makes cleaning easier, as carbon build up will not adhere to the non-reflective coated surface as much as it does on standard Parkerized finishes.

The MCSR V2 rail is a comfortable, extremely light weight modular rail system that will work in any situation as well as comfortably fit a suppressor inside the rail. The MCSR V2 was designed to make using a quick mounted suppressor easy to install or remove while inside the rail.
The MCSR V2 rail is designed so that the 3, 6, and 9 o'clock positions will now accept all keymod accessories and have two anti-rotation QD positions per side (6total). the internal dimension of the MCSR V2 has increased to 1.8" to accommodate most suppressors on the market.

title: For Sale:  Want an AR built? I'm your man!
postcontent:
Hey! Are you looking for someone to build a fully customized AR-15 for you? Really want one, but don't have the time? Or maybe you just don't know how to do it? Fret not, you've found your man right here! So you might ask yourself why you might want to have one built for you instead of just buying one, right? Well, here's your answer, it's a lot cheaper, and YOU get to choose exactly what's in and on it, instead of paying $1,000 for one and then dumping more money into making it how you want it. 

Economy isn't doing too great and my job has really cut down on hours, so I thought I might as well throw up this as a service to get a little extra money in. I've been doing this for a number of years and I'm completely competent on my work. If I wasn't confident I wouldn't be actively using my own build as a means to protect me and my family. 


Prices all depend on what you want. It can cost anywhere from as low as $700 or $800 or as high as $1300. I always send pictures and updates about how the rifle is coming, or if you'd like to learn you can be right there while it's being built. I would like payments to be in advance so that it gives me the proper money to get the parts in, or if you already have the parts you'll just be paying for labor which will differ depending on the rifle, I'll try to be low on the costs for labor as it's not really work for me, as it is fun. 

So throw an email at me and we'll see what we can work out! 

Have fun, and more importantly stay safe!
